{"title_page": "List of political parties in Mauritius", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Politics of Mauritius}}\nThis article lists [[Mauritius]] political parties in alphabetical order. Mauritius has a [[multi-party system]] with numerous [[political parties]], in which no one party often has a chance of gaining power alone, and parties must work with each other to form [[coalition government]]s.\n\n==The parties==\n<!--''The general rule on naming applies. That means: the parties are named in the English translation and the original native name is placed on the first line of the article unless the native form is more commonly used in English than the English form. Rationale and specifics: See: [[Wikipedia:Naming conventions (use English)]]''.-->\n\n=== Parties represented in the [[National Assembly of Mauritius]] ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:85%;text-align:center\"\n! colspan=2 | Name\n! Abbr.\n! Leader\n! MPs\n! Emblem\n! Actual<br />alliance\n! Website\n|-\n| style=\"background: {{Mouvement Socialiste Militant/meta/color}};\" |\n| [[Mouvement Socialiste Militant]] \n| MSM\n| [[Pravind Jugnauth]]\n| 37\n| \n| Alliance Morisien\n| [http://www.msmparty.com/ www.msmparty.com]\n|-\n| style=\"background: {{Labour Party (Mauritius)/meta/color}};\"|\n| [[Labour Party (Mauritius)|Labour Party]]\n| PTR\n| [[Navin Ramgoolam]]\n| 13\n| [[File:Logo of Labour Party (Mauritius).svg|23px]]\n| Alliance Nationale\n| [http://www.labourparty.mu/ www.labourparty.mu]\n|-\n| style=\"background: {{Mouvement Militant Mauricien/meta/color}};\" |\n| [[Mouvement Militant Mauricien]] \n| MMM\n| [[Paul Berenger]]\n| 9\n| [[File:Emblem of the MMM.jpg|23px]]\n| None\n| [http://www.mmm.mu/ www.mmm.mu]\n|-\n| style=\"background: {{Parti Mauricien Social-D\u00e9mocrate/meta/color}};\" |\n| [[Parti Mauricien Social D\u00e9mocrate]] \n| PMSD\n| [[Xavier-Luc Duval]]\n| 4\n| [[File:No image.png|60px]]\n| PTR/PMSD/MP\n| [http://lepmsd.mu/ lepmsd.mu]\n|-