{"title_page": "Demographics of South Africa", "text_new": "{{Use South African English|date=May 2012}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2012}}\n{{Infobox country demographics\n | country            = South Africa\n | image              = [[File:South-africa-demography.svg|300px]]\n | caption            = Population of South Africa, 1961\u20132017\n | size_of_population = 58,775,022 (2019 est.)<ref name=\"statssa_2019\" >{{Cite web |url=http://www.statssa.gov.za/?p=12362 |title=SA population reaches 58,8 million {{!}} Statistics South Africa |last=Africa |first=Statistics South |language=en-US |access-date=2020-03-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201212213/http://www.statssa.gov.za/?p=12362 |archive-date=1 February 2020 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n | density            = 48.1/km2\n | growth             = 1.43%<ref name=\"statssa2018\" />\n | birth              = 19.9 births/1,000 population (2019 est.)\n | death              = 9.2 deaths/1,000 population (2019 est.)\n | life               = 64.7 years (2019 est.)\n | life_male          = 61.5 years (2019 est.)\n | life_female        = 67.5 years (2019 est.)\n | infant_mortality   = 22.1 deaths/1,000 (2019 est.)\n | fertility          = 2.32 children born/woman (2019 est.)\n<!-- age structure (2019 est.) -->\n | age_0-14_years     = 28.8% (2019 est.)\n | age_15-64_years    = 65.2% (2019 est.)\n | age_65_years       = 6% (2019 est.)\n | total_mf_ratio     = 0.99 male(s)/female (2010 est.)\n | sr_at_birth        = 1.02 male(s)/female\n | sr_under_15        = 1 male(s)/female\n | sr_15-64_years     = 1.02 male(s)/female\n | sr_65_years_over   = 0.68 male(s)/female\n<!-- nationality -->\n | nation             = South African\n | major_ethnic       =\n | minor_ethnic       =\n\n | official           = See [[Languages of South Africa]]\n | spoken             =\n}}\n[[File:South Africa population density map.svg|thumb|Population density in South Africa (darker color = higher density)]]\nThe population of [[South Africa]] is about 58.8 million people of diverse origins, cultures, languages, and religions.<ref name=\"statssa_2019\" /><ref name=\"statssa2018\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.statssa.gov.za/publications/P0302/P03022018.pdf|title=Mid - year population estimates|date=23 July 2018|website=Stats SA|publisher=[[Statistics South Africa]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180723182517/http://www.statssa.gov.za/publications/P0302/P03022018.pdf|archive-date=23 July 2018|url-status=live|accessdate=23 July 2018}}</ref> The [[South African National Census of 2011|2011 South African census]] was the last held and the next will be in 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.statssa.gov.za/?p=11323|title=Census 2021 New Methodologies Test|date=20 July 2018|website=Statistics South Africa (Stats SA)|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180804010519/http://www.statssa.gov.za/?p=11323|archive-date=4 August 2018|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, [[Statistics South Africa]] counted 2.1 million foreigners in total.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.statssa.gov.za/publications/P03014/P030142011.pdf|title=Table 3.5, Statistical release (Revised) P0301.4, Census 2011|website=Statssa.gov.za|accessdate=25 July 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151113203528/http://www.statssa.gov.za/publications/P03014/P030142011.pdf|archivedate=13 November 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref> However, reports{{specify}} suggest that is an underestimation. The real figure may be as high as five million,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.economist.com/node/11399350|title=Nowhere left to go|date=20 May 2008|website=Economist.com|accessdate=29 August 2017|via=The Economist}}</ref> including some three million [[Demographics of Zimbabwe|Zimbabweans]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.sky.com/story/573086/escape-from-mugabe-zimbabwes-exodus |title=Escape From Mugabe: Zimbabwe's Exodus |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160124000311/http://news.sky.com/story/573086/escape-from-mugabe-zimbabwes-exodus |archivedate=24 January 2016 |df=dmy }}</ref>\n\n==Population==\n===Censuses===\n====1904 Census====\nSouth African Population Figures for the 1904 Census. Source:<ref name=\"Smuts\">Smuts I: The Sanguine Years 1870\u20131919, W.K. Hancock, Cambridge University Press, 1962, pg 219</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" cellspacing=\"10\" cellpadding=\"0\" style=\"width:80%;\"\n|- style=\"text-align:center\"\n! {{diagonal split header|Pop. Group|Colony}}\n|  style=\"width:15%; background:mistyrose;\"|'''[[Cape Colony]]'''\n|  style=\"width:15%; background:mistyrose;\"|'''[[Colony of Natal|Natal]]'''\n|  style=\"width:15%; background:moccasin;\"|'''[[Transvaal Colony|Transvaal]]'''\n|  style=\"width:15%; background:moccasin;\"| '''[[Orange River Colony|Orange River<br> Colony]]'''\n! Total\n! Percent\n|- style=\"text-align:right; background:gainsboro;\"\n|  style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Bantu peoples in South Africa|African]]\n|  &nbsp;1,424,787\n|  904,041\n|  937,127\n|  225,101\n|  '''3,491,056'''\n|  67.5%\n|- style=\"text-align:right; background:white;\"\n|  style=\"text-align:left; \"|[[White South Africans|White]]\n|  579,741\n|  97,109\n|  297,277\n|  142,690\n|  '''1,116,805'''\n|  21.6%\n|- style=\"text-align:right; background:#eee;\"\n|  style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Coloureds|Coloured]]\n|  395,034\n|  6,686\n|  24,226\n|  19,282\n|  '''445,228'''\n|  8.6%\n|- style=\"text-align:right; background:#EEEEE0\"\n|  style=\"text-align:left; \"|[[Indian South Africans|Indian]]\n| 10,242\n| 100,918\n|  11,321\n|  253\n|  '''122,734'''\n|  2.4%\n|- style=\"text-align:right; background:honeydew;\"\n|  style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''Total'''\n|  '''2,409,804'''\n|  '''1,108,754'''\n|  '''1,269,951'''\n|  '''387,315'''\n|  '''5,175,463'''\n|  100.0%\n|- style=\"text-align:right; background:mintcream;\"\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|% of S. Africa\n| 46.6%\n| 21.4%\n| 24.5%\n| 7.5%\n| 100%\n|\n|}\n\n====1960 Census====\nSources: ''[[Statesman's 