n|percentages = pagr\n|footnote    = \n|source      = [[United Nations Secretariat]]<ref>{{cite web |title=World Population Prospects 2019: Data Booklet |url=https://population.un.org/wpp/Publications/Files/WPP2019_DataBooklet.pdf |publisher=United Nations Department of Economic and Social Affairs Population Dynamics |accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n|2019|\t58558000\n|2030|\t65956000\n|2050|\t75518000\n|2100|\t79191000\n}}\n\n===Age and population estimates: 1950 to 2015===\nAccording to the 2010 revision of the [[United Nations Secretariat]]'s ''World Population Prospects'', South Africa's total population was 50,133,000 in 2010, compared to only 13,683,000 in 1950. In 2010, 30.1% of the people were children under the age of 15, 65.2% were between 15 and 64 years of age, and 4.6% were 65 or older.<ref name=\"WPP 2010\">[http://esa.un.org/unpd/wpp/index.htm Population Division of the Department of Economic and Social Affairs of the United Nations Secretariat, World Population Prospects: The 2010 Revision] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110506065230/http://esa.un.org/unpd/wpp/index.htm |date=6 May 2011 }}</ref> ''All population estimates are rounded to the nearest thousand.''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"width:54%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:6%;\"|Year\n! style=\"width:12%;\"|Total population\n! style=\"width:12%;\"|Percentage<br> under 15<br> years old\n! style=\"width:12%;\"|Percentage<br> 15 to 64 <br> years old\n! style=\"width:12%;\"|Percentage<br> at least 65 <br> years old\n|-\n| 1950\n|13,683,000||38.6||57.8||3.6\n|-\n| 1955\n|15,385,000||39.9||56.4||3.8\n|-\n| 1960\n|17,396,000||40.9||55.2||3.9\n|-\n| 1965\n|19,814,000||41.9||54.2||3.9\n|-\n| 1970\n|22,502,000||42.1||54.5||3.4\n|-\n| 1975\n|25,699,000||41.9||54.9||3.2\n|-\n| 1980\n|29,077,000||41.5||55.3||3.1\n|-\n| 1985\n|32,983,000||40.5||56.4||3.1\n|-\n| 1990\n|36,794,000||38.9||57.9||3.2\n|-tyt,7ik ,iy,tj\n| 1995\n|41,402,000||36.0||60.6||3.4\n|-\n| 2000\n|44,760,000||33.7||62.6||3.7\n|-\n| 2005\n|47,793,000||31.7||64.2||4.1\n|-\n| 2010\n|50,133,000||30.1||65.2||4.6\n|-\n| 2015\n|54,490,000||29.2||63.0||7.7 \n|}\n\n==Vital statistics==\n===Stats SA: From 2002 to present===\nThe following statistics are obtained from the mid-year population estimates published by [[Statistics South Africa|Stats SA]]:<ref>{{Cite web|title=Archived publications for: P0302|url=http://www.statssa.gov.za/?page_id=1866&PPN=P0302&SCH=7668|website=www.statssa.gov.za|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! \n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|Average population \n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|Live births\n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|Deaths\n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|Natural change\n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|Crude birth rate (per 1,000)\n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|Crude death rate (per 1,000)\n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|Natural change (per 1,000)\n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|[[Total fertility rate]]s\n|-\n| 2002\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 1,118,916\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 608,480\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 510,436\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 24,5 \n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 13,3 \n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 11,2 \n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 2.45\n|-\n| 2003\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 1,127,380\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 643,285\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 484,095\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 24,4 \n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 13,9 \n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 10,5 \n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 2.42\n|-\n| 2004\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| \n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 1,134,751\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 671,101\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 463,650\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 24,3 \n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 14,4\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 9,9 \n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 2.54\n|-\n|  2005\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| \n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 1,141,351\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 682,059\n| style=\