{"title_page": "Bava Nachadu", "text_new": "{{short description|2001 film by K. S. Ravikumar}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=July 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Bava Nachadu\n| image          = Bava_Nachadu.jpg\n| imdb_id        =\n| writer         = Janardhan Maharshi<br />{{small|(story / dialogues)}}\n| screenplay     = K. S. Ravikumar\n| producer       = M. Arjuna Raju\n| director       = [[K. S. Ravikumar]]\n| starring       = [[Akkineni Nagarjuna|Nagarjuna Akkineni]]<br>[[Simran (actress)|Simran]]<br>[[Reema Sen]]\n| music          = [[M. M. Keeravani]]\n| cinematography = [[Shyam K. Naidu]]\n| editing        = Cola Bhaskar\n| studio         = Roja Movies\n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|2001|06|07|df=y}}\n| runtime        = 146 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n| awards         = \n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n\n'''''Bava Nachadu''''' is a 2001 [[Cinema of Andhra Pradesh|Tollywood]] film produced by M. Arjuna Raju under the Roja Movies banner, written and directed by [[K. S. Ravikumar]]. It stars [[Akkineni Nagarjuna|Nagarjuna Akkineni]], [[Simran (actress)|Simran]] and [[Reema Sen]] in the lead roles, with music scored by [[M. M. Keeravani]].<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-bavanachadu.html|title=Movie Riview Bava Nachadu|publisher= idlebrain.com |accessdate= 19 November 2012}}</ref> The Hindi version of the film is ''Naya Ghulam''.{{Citation needed|date=November 2012}} The film is a flop at the box office.{{citation needed|date=June 2017}}\n\n==Plot==\nAjay ([[Akkineni Nagarjuna|Nagarjuna Akkineni]]) is an adman (director and actor) who has a definite idea about how his future wife should be. He marries a village belle Meenakshi ([[Simran (actress)|Simran]]), handpicked by his mother from her native town Kovvuru. Meenakshi soon becomes pregnant. Some time later, Meenakshi meets with a hairline fracture. Her entire family lands up at Ajay's house to take care of Meenakshi. She has a beautiful and greedy sister called Lahari ([[Reema Sen]]). During that period Suma ([[Suman Ranganathan]]), the regular model of Ajay meets with a fracture and Lahari replaces her as the model opposite Ajay. Lahari is lured by the modeling profession and then falls in love with Ajay. But Ajay does not have any feelings for her. Meenakshi gets well and her family returns to their village. Lahari tells Meenakshi about her desire to marry Ajay. Meenakshi gets mad and returns home to her husband. Meanwhile, Lahari attempts suicide. Meenakshi, being very close to Lahari, promises Lahari that she will get her married to Ajay. The rest of the film is about how Ajay manages to save his marriage without hurting Lahari and how he gets Meenakshi back.\n\n==Cast==\n\n*[[Akkineni Nagarjuna|Nagarjuna Akkineni]] as Ajay\n*[[Simran (actress)|Simran]] as Meenakshi\n*[[Reema Sen]] as Lahari\n*[[Suman Ranganathan]] as Suma\n*[[Tanikella Bharani]]\n*[[Mallikarjuna Rao (actor)|Mallikarjuna Rao]]\n*[[M. S. Narayana]]\n*[[Sudha (Telugu actress)|Sudha]]\t\n*Raja Ravindra\n*Janardhan Maharshi\n*Ananth\n*Manorama\n*Rajitha\n*[[K. S. Ravikumar]] (cameo)\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Bava Nachadu\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = [[M. M. Keeravani]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 2001\n| recorded   =2001\n| genre      = Soundtrack\n| length     = 30:37\n| label      = Supreme Music<br/>[[Aditya Music]]\n| producer   = M. M. Keeravani\n| prev_title = [[Student No.1]]\n| prev_year  = 2001\n| next_title = [[Akasa Veedhilo]]\n| next_year  = 2001\n}}\nThe music was composed by [[M. M. Keeravani]]. Music released on SUPREME Audio company.\n\n{{Track listing\n| collapsed =\n| headline = Track_List\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| total_length = 30:37\n| title1  = Anuragam Anuragamlo\n| lyrics1 = [[Chandrabose (lyricist)|Chandrabose]] \n| extra1  = [[Hariharan (singer)|Hariharan]], [[Sujatha Mohan|Sujatha]]\n| length1 = 5:22\n\n| title2  = Chandamama Chandamama\n| lyrics2 = Chandrabose\n| extra2  = [[Udit Narayan]], [[K. S. Chithra|Chitra]], [[Harini (singer)|Harini]]\n| length2 = 4:49\n\n| title3  = Matotundhi Magada\n| lyrics3 = [[Sirivennela Seetarama Sastry]]\n| extra3  = [[Shankar Mahadevan]], [[Anuradha Sriram]]\n| length3 = 5:31\n\n| title4  = Akka Bava Nachada\n| lyrics4 = [[Veturi Sundararama Murthy]]\n| extra4  = Harini\n| length4 = 4:34\n\n| title5  = Bang Bang\n| lyrics5 = Sirivennela Seetarama Sastry\n| extra5  = Shankar Mahadevan, [[Suneeta Rao]] \n| length5 = 5:09\n\n| title6  = Very Sexy\n| lyrics6 =Chandrabose\n| extra6  = Shankar Mahadevan, Ganga\n| length6 = 5:12\n}}\n\n==Reception==\nThe film received a mixed reception. Many declared the movie to be an outright drama with little or no logic at all. However, the movie fared well mainly due to the lack of any other quality cinema at that time and also of Simran's glamour and Nagarjuna's popularity.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|1604887|Bava Nachadu}}\n\n{{K. S. Ravikumar}}\n\n[[Category:2001 films]]\n[[Category:Telugu-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by K. S. Ravikumar]]\n[[Category:Films scored by M. M. Keeravani]]\n[[Category:2000s Telugu-language films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2001 film by K. S. Ravikumar}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=July 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Bava Nachadu\n| image          = Bava_Nachadu.jpg\n| imdb_id        =\n| writer         = Janardhan Maharshi<br />{{small|(story / dialogues)}}\n| screenplay     = K. S. Ravikumar\n| producer       = M. Arjuna Raju\n| director       = [[K. S. Ravikumar]]\n| starring       = [[Akkineni Nagarjuna|Nagarjuna Akkineni]]<br>[[Simran (actress)|Simran]]<br>[[Reema Sen]]\n| music          = [[M. M. Keeravani]]\n| cinematography = [[Shyam K. Naidu]]\n| editing        = Cola Bha