{"title_page": "Fire and Gasoline", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Fire and Gasoline\n| type       = [[Studio Album]]\n| artist     = [[Steve Jones (musician)|Steve Jones]]\n| cover      = Fire_and_Gasoline.jpeg\n| alt        =\n| released   = 1989\n| recorded   = 1989; Amigo Studios, [[Los Angeles, California]]\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Hard rock]], [[Heavy metal music|Heavy metal]]\n| length     = 49:20\n| label      = [[Music Corporation of America|MCA]]\n| producer   = [http://www.dearnley.com/ Mark Dearnley],<ref>allmusic.com & album cover</ref>[[Ian Astbury]]\n| prev_title = [[Mercy (Steve Jones album)|Mercy]]\n| prev_year  = 1987\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n|rev1 = [[Allmusic]]\n|rev1score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>[{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r10591|pure_url=yes}} Allmusic review]</ref>\n}}<!-- Automatically generated by DASHBot-->\n\n'''''Fire and Gasoline''''' is a [[Heavy metal music|heavy metal]] album released in 1989 by [[United Kingdom|British]] [[musician]] [[Steve Jones (musician)|Steve Jones]], formerly of the [[Sex Pistols]]. The album featured [[Axl Rose]] of [[Guns N' Roses]] on the song \"I Did U No Wrong\" and the lyrics of [[Nikki Sixx]] of [[M\u00f6tley Cr\u00fce]] on \"We're Not Saints\". The album was co-produced by [[Ian Astbury]] of [[The Cult]], who also sings backing vocals on the album, while Cult guitarist [[Billy Duffy]] plays guitar on the song \"Get Ready\" and then-current Cult drummer [[Mickey Curry]] plays throughout the album.\n\n==Reception==\nIn 2005, ''Fire and Gasoline'' was ranked number 460 in ''Rock Hard'' magazine's book of ''The 500 Greatest Rock & Metal Albums of All Time''.<ref>{{cite book|last=[...]|first=Rock Hard (Hrsg.). [Red.: Michael Rensen. Mitarb.: G\u00f6tz K\u00fchnemund]|title=Best of Rock & Metal die 500 st\u00e4rksten Scheiben aller Zeiten|year=2005|publisher=Heel|location=K\u00f6nigswinter|isbn=3-89880-517-4|page=24}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n